# Timber 2.x & Twig 3 — Guardrails

The theme ships **Timber 2.4** via Composer (`vendor/timber/timber`).
History: mixing it with the `timber-library` WP.org plugin (Timber 1.x) and
over-aggressive Twig filter registration caused two critical-error fatals.
These rules keep it stable.

## 1 — Never install the Timber 1.x plugin

Keep `.wp-env.json` plugins to ACF + Contact Form 7. If `timber-library`
sneaks in, `Timber\Timber::init()` resolves to the **protected** 1.x method
and every page 500s. `functions.php` has a guard that surfaces an admin
notice, but the fix is to remove the plugin:

```bash
npm run wp:cli -- plugin deactivate timber-library.latest-stable
npx wp-env run cli -- rm -rf /var/www/html/wp-content/plugins/timber-library.latest-stable
```

## 2 — Controller → Twig pattern

```php
// archive-case_study.php
$context = Timber::context();
$context['posts'] = Timber::get_posts();
Timber::render( 'archive-case_study.twig', $context );
```

Templates live in `views/` and `views/partials/` (search path set in
`functions.php`). Keep PHP files skinny; put reusable logic in `src/`.

## 3 — Registering Twig filters / functions (the tricky one)

`timber/twig` can fire more than once per request. Twig 3 throws
`LogicException` if:
- a filter/function name is re-registered, **or**
- the `Environment`'s extensions are already initialized (e.g. because
  something called `getFilter()` / `getFunction()` on it).

✅ Correct pattern — register once, swallow re-registration safely:

```php
add_filter( 'timber/twig', function ( \Twig\Environment $twig ) {
    try {
        $twig->addFilter( new \Twig\TwigFilter( 'excerpt', /* fn */ ) );
    } catch ( \LogicException $e ) {
        // already registered or extensions frozen — no-op
    }
    return $twig;
} );
```

❌ Wrong — these cause the fatals we already fixed:

```php
if ( null === $twig->getFilter( 'excerpt' ) ) { ... }   // freezes extensions
$twig->addFilter( new \Twig\TwigFilter( 'truncate', ... ) ); // clashes with Timber's
static $registered = false; if ( $registered ) return;   // unreliable across contexts
```

## 4 — Naming

Use bespoke filter names (`excerpt`, not `truncate`) so they never collide
with Timber or `twig/extra` built-ins (`truncate`, `length`, `u.*`, etc.).

## 5 — Twig authoring

- Timber context helpers: `{{ post.title }}`, `{{ post.thumbnail.src('hero-image') }}`.
- Menus come from `{{ menu_primary.items }}` / `{{ menu_footer.items }}`.
- Global ACF options live at `{{ options.phone }}`, `{{ options.social_linkedin }}`, etc.
- Escape by default; mark HTML-safe helpers with `is_safe: ['html']` (see `icon()`).
